article.headline: Marist 78, Delaware 62
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Marist had four players in double figures, and the Red Foxes pulled away in the second half for a 78-62 win over Delaware Tuesday night. Marist (1-1) connected on 54 percent of its shots from the field, and landed 8 of 20 three-pointers. Will Whittington led Marist with 20 points and added three rebounds. Jared Jordan contributed 17 points, and Ryan Stillphen and James Smith each scored 15 points. Smith also grabbed a game-high 10 rebounds. Herb Courtney scored a game-high 27 points for the Delaware (0-1). Sam McMahon grabbed a team-high six rebounds.
